    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ensure that knives sold in UK shops are locked away in secure cabinets.",
        "additional_details": "Official statistics show an increase of 47.5% in knife-related offences in 34 English and Welsh counties between April 2010 and September 2018.\r\n\r\nThis compared with an 11% knife crime rise\u00a0within the capital.\r\n\r\nThe BBC tracked the first 100 homicides of 2019 and found that 40 of those were stabbings, 23 were unknown and 37 were other. \r\n\r\nThe statistics alone are terrifying and something needs to be done to help prevent this from happening, especially at such an alarming rate.\r\n\r\nSayNoToKnives.",
        "background": "As of right now, in 2019, it is legal for knives to be sold without being locked away in secure cabinets, meaning that anyone, including those underage, can pick a knife up off the shelf and steal it. The epidemic of knife crime in the UK recently means that this needs to change.",
